Fix concurrency issues in OnheapIncrementalIndex * Was encountering weird errors when fast writes were coming in while queries were happening. * Now pre-allocates an array for the row aggregates  but only populates them as null * Allows lazy filling in of the array * If values are not making it into the array fast enough  the metric getters return their empty values (0 or null)

Fix bad distribution of cache keys across nodes  With the existing hash function some nodes could end up with 3 times the number of keys as others. The following changes improve that to roughly less than 5% differences across nodes.  - switch from fnv-1a to murmur3_128 hash - increase repetitions for ketama algorithm - test to analyze distribution  Also updates spymemcached for recent bugfixes

Update systemd service unit configurations.  Accept the return of exit code 143 and 130 as these are the default return codes for the standard way of stopping druid (either with a SIGKILL  SIGINT  or SIGTERM).  This is intended to be a temporary fix until [this](https://github.com/druid-io/druid/issues/1378) bug is resolved.

Update custom define type spec.  Allow for either a string or integer in the response error message from a test that is expected to fail.  This fixes mixed response types base on the system the test is being preformed on.

Associate groupBy v2 resources with the Sequence lifecycle.
